# Knowledge Base Design

## Purpose

The Knowledge Base (KB) stores reusable pentesting knowledge that informs engagement defaults and suggestions.

## Knowledge Types

### Reference

* Port → Service mappings
* Protocol descriptions

### Methodology

* Phase definitions
* Expected inputs/outputs

### Techniques / Playbooks

* Testing steps
* Tool suggestions
* Required inputs

## Knowledge Entry Structure

* id
* type (reference | methodology | technique)
* title
* content (markdown)
* tags

## KB Capabilities (MVP)

* Create/edit/delete entries
* Tagging
* Full-text search

## KB → Engagement Interaction

* Ports map to services
* Services map to techniques
* Techniques are suggested by rules
